# Collaboration Convergence Notes (Optional)

This document is optional and separate from mandatory development rules.
Use it only when running document-convergence rounds.

## Scope
- Convergence and batch-merge operation notes
- Pending batch handling guidance
- Short Form synchronization workflow notes

## Frozen Operation (Moved from collaboration-rules.mdc)
This document context may be in a frozen operating state. Outside an approved release window, direct edits to the main rules body are prohibited.
New change requests should be collected as `Pending` items and must not be merged into the main body until batch approval is completed in an approved release window.

## Optional Guidance
1. In frozen state, convergence outputs can be recorded as `Pending Batch` proposals.
2. Higher-priority runtime instructions may still be translated into proposals without immediate body merge.
3. During release-window updates, review and synchronize any derived summary sections with the main body.

## Non-Normative
This file does not override `collaboration-rules.mdc`.
If any conflict exists, follow `collaboration-rules.mdc`.
